gy studies, Beauregard lays out a framework that acknowledges the inevitable insufficiency of our representations of reality while also engaging more holistically with the world in all of its diversity—including human and nonhuman actors alike.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aCity planningzUnited States. 0aCity planning. 7aARCHITECTURE / General.2bisacsh  aarchitectural criticism, social philosophy, urban planning, land use, city planners, highway interchanges, retention ponds, zoning documents, conference rooms, materiality, weather patterns, plants and animals, regulatory technologies, new materialist perspective, nonhuman things, actor-network theory, science, technology studies, human world, perception, sociology, civic duty, thought experiment, preservation.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG and UP eBook Package 2000-2015z978311063872108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z97831106904390 cprintz978022629725540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226297422423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226297422/original  a978-3-11-063872-1  DG and UP eBook Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  a978-3-11-069043-9  University of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles